              line-height: 1.5;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">US freezes funds for more universities</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Cornell and Northwestern universities had their funding frozen over civil rights violations. </strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The US has frozen over <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-h3-4-1B-in-federal-funding?source=website" target="_blank">$1B in federal funding</a> to Cornell University and about $790M to Northwestern University amid investigations into alleged civil rights violations. The funding pause primarily affects grants and contracts from the Department of Defense, Health, Education, and Agriculture. The Universities stated they’d received minimal information about the fund freeze. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In a statement on Tuesday, Cornell University said it received 75 stop-work orders from the Department of Defense, halting the ongoing research. The move is part of a broader crackdown by the Trump administration on US universities. Last month, it sent a letter to 60 schools, including Cornell and Northwestern, warning that the government could take appropriate measures if it found these schools did not address anti-Semitism.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">In addition to frozen funds, federal agents have also <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-h3-5-detained-and-deported?source=website" target="_blank">detained and deported</a> foreign student protesters, raising concerns about Islamophobia and political suppression amid the ongoing Israel-Gaza war.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
