                    "><strong>Ukraine captured two Chinese nationals fighting for Russia in Donetsk, raising concerns about possible Chinese involvement in the war</strong>. President Zelensky suggested more Chinese fighters may be present, prompting Ukraine to summon China’s chargé d'affaires for an explanation. Kyiv said such involvement contradicts China’s stated neutrality. Beijing denied the allegations, saying it’s verifying the situation and has consistently urged its citizens to steer away from an armed conflict against Ukraine (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br1-6-more-details?source=website" target="_blank">more details</a>).</p>
                    
