                    "><strong>Pakistan has stepped up deportations of Afghan refugees, expelling nearly 9,000 since April 1</strong> after a deadline for undocumented Afghans to vacate expired. The Taliban government has condemned the crackdown as violent and politically motivated, while human rights groups warn it puts refugees at considerable risk. Tensions between Islamabad and Kabul have escalated, with Pakistan blaming the Taliban for failing to curb cross-border militancy (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br2-7-read-more?source=website" target="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
