              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>Trump announced a 90-day pause on retaliatory tariffs for most countries, reducing them to a 10% blanket, excluding China</strong>, whose tariffs were increased to 125%. China has imposed steep 84% tariffs on all US goods. The move marks a partial retreat from Trump’s aggressive trade stance, aiming to stabilize markets while maintaining a hardline position on China (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br4-9-updated-tariff-list?source=website" target="_blank">updated tariff list</a>).</p>
