              border-left: 3px solid #4D3060;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>The US has withdrawn from UN shipping decarbonization talks in London, opposing proposed greenhouse gas emission fees on ships</strong>. Citing unfair treatment, Washington warned of possible reciprocal measures. Despite the move, the International Maritime Organization continues negotiations, with countries like the EU pushing for a carbon levy to help the shipping industry reach net zero by 2050 (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br3-8-carbon-clash?source=website" target="_blank">carbon clash</a>).</p>
