                    "><strong>​​Samsung's Ballie robot is finally set to launch this summer in the US and South Korea, powered by Google's Gemini AI</strong>. The updated Ballie can process voice, audio, and visual data to manage smart home devices and give health or style tips. However, the pricing is still unknown, possibly due to the sweeping tariffs. Samsung first teased Ballie in 2020, with the first version demoed at the Consumer Electronics Show (CES) in Las Vegas in 2024 (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br6-11-product-details?source=website" target="_blank">product details</a>).</p>
