                    "><strong>Scientists have created special brain cells that helped restore movement in rats with Parkinson's-like symptoms</strong>. Made from human stem cells and altered with eight genes, these cells have an “invisibility cloak” that helps them evade the immune system. The breakthrough could lead to newer treatments for diseases like Parkinson’s and diabetes without needing immune-suppressing drugs (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-10-04-2025-br7-12-one-cell-fits-all?source=website" target="_blank">one cell fits all</a>).</p>
